22. Simple Notification Service

An AWS service that allows you to automate the sending of email or text msgs based on events that happen in your AWS account.
Coordinates and manages the delivery or sending of messages to subscribing endpoints or clients.

Two types of clients: publishers and subscribers

Publishers asynchronously communicate with subscribers by producing and sending a message to a topic when they're subscribed to a topic.

SNS Benefits:
Send automated/manual notifications
Send notification to email, mobile, and HTTP endpoints
Closely integrated with other AWS services so that alarms, events, and actions in your AWS can trigger your notifications.

Can set this up in a matter of minutes, easy to use.
